<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11121l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11121l">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11121l"> 121(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> after 1815 imperialists oblige / Chat to hang out white line</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Bassesses politiques</b> C&apos;est merveille en France que la contagion, et l&apos;on crierait A bas ma t&ecirc;te! si on l&apos;entendait crier &agrave; son voisin. Les imp&eacute;rialistes entraient jusque dans nos maisons et nous faisaient, nous autres bourbonistes, exposer en drapeau sans tache les restes de blanc renferm&eacute;s dans nos lingeries, c&apos;est ce qui arriva chez moi; mais madame de Chateaubriand n&apos;y voulut entendre, et d&eacute;fendit vaillamment ses mousselines. <br><font color="green">[Political baseness: It is amazing in France the way things spread: people would shout &ldquo;down with my head!&rdquo; if they heard their neighbours shouting it. The imperialists used to come right into our houses and make us Bourbonists display as stainless flags leftover bits of white material shut up with our linen. This happened at my house, but Mme de Chateaubriand would not hear of it and valiantly defended her muslin.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) III, <i> M&eacute;moires d&apos;Outre-tombe.</i> 102</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
